    <section class="bg-white border-b py-8" id="faq">
      <div class="container mx-auto flex flex-wrap pt-4 pb-12">
        <h2 class="w-full my-2 text-5xl font-bold leading-tight text-center text-gray-800">
          FAQ
        </h2>
        <div class="w-full mb-4 p-6">
          <div class="mb-6">
            <p class="text-2xl font-thin leading-none mb-2">
              How many apps can I register on mlAuth?
            </p>
            <p class="">
              You can register as many apps as you want.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <p class="text-2xl font-thin leading-none mb-2">
              How do I differentiate my development and production apps?
            </p>
            <p class="">
              You can create development apps and work on them for as long as possible. When you feel like going into production, you can either update the app's status, or create a separate production app.
              <br>
              For security reasons, production apps can only be accessed via the secure 'https' protocol.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <p class="text-2xl font-thin leading-none mb-2">
              My production app requests are returning a 404 status code with a 'app not found' message, why is that?
            </p>
            <p class="">
              For security reasons, production apps can only be accessed via the secure 'https' protocol.
              <br>
              If you tried to access a production app with your app's valid keys, mlAuth interprets that as a security issue and changes your app keys to prevent possible security breaches.
              <br>
              All you need to fix is open your dashboard and change your app keys.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

